docs.lead_paragraph: THE TEHUANTEPEC ROUTE.--The bark Rapid, Capt. MAROHANT, arrived to-day from Vera Cruz. She is the vessel that took from this port in July last, the 200 workmen for the Tehuantepec Road. Capt. M. reports that they all arrived in good health, and that in his opinion Mr. MURPHY, the overseer, understands and is well calculated for that business. He embarked all his men up the river.

headline.main: A Growing Evil in the Mines--Malaria.

docs.lead_paragraph: From the Sacramento Ber. The mountains of California have become proverbial for the salubrity of their climate. Even in the Winters of '49, '50 and '51, when the comforts of life were seldom met with and the necessaries were no easily obtained, the destruction of human life by discases, engendered, was astonishingly small, and sickness was comparatively unknown in those regions.
